<IN>
HEALTH CARE PROVIDERS, MEDICINE, DENTISTRY (HEA)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   SANTA MONICA, Calif. -- National Medical Enterprises Inc.,
a health care concern, said it will redeem on Oct. 15 all
extendable notes, due 1999, that haven't been tendered for
repayment on or before Oct. 1.
   The company has $98 million of the notes outstanding. It
issued the notes in October 1984. National Medical said it
will redeem the notes at 100% of the principal amount.
Interest accrued through Oct. 14 will be paid to notes of
record Sept. 30. The current interest rate is 9.4%, and the
current interest-rate period expires Oct. 14.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Note holders' option of tendering for repayment arises
when a new interest period and rate for the extendable notes
is established. Under terms of the notes, the company must
establish a new interest period and rate for a five-year
period beginning Oct. 15. National Medical has set an
interest rate of 8.65% for the coming five-year period.
</TEXT>
