   WestAir also announced cutbacks in service that will
result in the termination of 99 of its about 2,780 employees.
Included are 25 customer-service personnel and 24 pilots. In
addition, 50 pilots are set to be furloughed as the result of
schedule adjustments in California, WestAir said.
   The company added that it plans to retire a dozen aircraft
by year end, replacing them with more fuel-efficient models.
Currently, the company has a fleet of about 100 aircraft.
