<HL>
   Pikeville National Acquisition
</HL>
<DATE>
09/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9B
</SO>
<CO>
   PKVL
</CO>
<IN>
EASTERN U.S. BANKS (BAE)
BANKS (BNK)
STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   PIKEVILLE, Ky. -- Pikeville National Corp. said it agreed
in principle to acquire First Federal Savings Bank, of
Campbellsville, Ky. Terms weren't disclosed.
   In connection with the acquisition, Pikeville National
said it intends to issue and sell about 120,000 shares of its
common stock. Proceeds of the sale, expected to be
approximately $3 million, will be contributed to the capital
of First Federal, Pikeville said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The conversion and the merger will be subject to approvals
of various regulatory agencies, Pikeville said.
